PHP  
•	Is an abbreviation for PHP Hypertext Pre-processor
•	Is widely used, open source scripting language 
•	Scripts are implemented on the server 
•	Runs on numerous platforms such as Windows, Linux, UNIX, Mas OS etc.
•	Well-matched with just about all servers such as Apache, IIS etc.
•	Supports extensive range of databases 
•	Easy to learn 
•	Runs effectively on the server side
Basic PHP Syntax
PHP script stars with <?php and ends with ?>. And can be placed anywhere in the document. File extension of the PHP files is .php. PHP file normally contain HTML tags and some PHP scripting code.
Ex:
<html>
<head>
<title>Basic01</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>My first PHP page</h1>
<?php
echo "Hello World"; // echo – is output display tag
?>
</body>
</html>
